<h3 id="head-e6db30625570998f4745678830b5eb62ed59534c">Antimagic Realm</h3>

    <ul>

 Cost: 10 
        <ul>

        <li>
<p>
Add to Blows 
</p>
</li>
        <li>
<p>
Add to Speed 
</p>
</li>
        <li>
<p>
Add to Life 
</p>
</li>
        <li>
<p>
Vampiric Brand 
</p>
</li>
        <li>
<p>
Chaos Brand 
</p>
</li>
        <li>
<p>
Reflection 
</p>
</li>
        <li>
<p>
Free Action 
</p>
</li>
        <li>
<p>
Hold Life 
</p>
</li>
        <li>
<p>
No Teleportation 
</p>
</li>
        <li>
<p>
See Invisible 
</p>
</li>
        <li>
<p>
Anti-magic shell, as per Amulet of Anti-magic 
</p>
</li>
        <li>
<p>
Antimagic field, similar to a Dark Sword's, but with maximum strength 10% at Antimagic skill level 50 (compare with 50% for normal Dark Sword).  Cumulative with Dark Sword's antimagic field, and with the following power. 
</p>
</li>
        <li>
<p>
Antimagic field with maximum strength 20%, as per above.  Cumulative with Dark Sword's antimagic field, and with the preceding power. 
</p>
</li>

        </ul>    </ul>


<h2 id="head-ff11f0da0a4cd245270f188d8a7299b4084d0328">Chatter</h2>
<p>
<a href="./FeathinSilyar">FeathinSilyar</a>:  First off, credit to Lord Dimwit for posting the realms code, and Ornedan for posting power gaining code, <a class="external" href=".www.t-o-m-e.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=2192"><img src="./wiki/rightsidebar/img/moin-www.png" alt="[WWW]" height="11" width="11">both in this thread</a>. 
</p>
<p>
Whoever knows exactly what those last three flags in Antimagic Realm are, please go ahead and translate them. 
</p>

    <ul>

 <strong><a href="./ZizzoTheInfinite">ZizzoTheInfinite</a></strong>:  Is the above suitable? 
        <ul>

  <a href="./FeathinSilyar">FeathinSilyar</a>:  Yup, thanks Zizzo. <p>
  The experience gaining is not based on code but observation.  If it can better be represented by something different, go ahead. 
</p>

        </ul>    </ul>


<p>
<a href="./ElIott">ElIott</a>:  Wow.  I don't think I've ever even seen a weapon get any of the Realms above Earth, though the fact that the weapon's Realm's don't show up in the dump doesn't help.  Having a weapon get Precognition would be, umm... useful. 
</p>

    <ul>

 <a href="./FeathinSilyar">FeathinSilyar</a>:  I got the Mind realm recently, on one of the three daggers.  But yeah, the higher realms are incredibly rare, and quite possibly not even possible due to the way the coding works.  There were comments about that in the forum thread mentioned above that I got the coding from for this spoiler.  I think we should make a subpage of this one for "bragging" about sentient weapons developped, so people can see just what sentient weapons tend to turn out like.  I think earthquakes is over-feared, as I've levelled quite a few sentient weapons very high without getting that brand. 
        <ul>

  <strong><a href="./RedNaga">RedNaga</a></strong>: i've only seen the Chaos realm once (and it was on Mormegil...), and none of the other higher, but as far as earthquake goes... i've once found all three 'thanc and Mormegil with a single character, and <strong>*all four got the earthquake flag before level 30!!*</strong><br>
 
        </ul>    </ul>


<p>
The discussion thread about the levelling of sentient weapons seem like a nice idea - oh and - it is really possible to find Garachoth? It has the SPECIAL_GENE flag and i've never seen it in any special level or guardian (unless it appear in the Void, where i never dared to try) 
</p>

            <ul>

   <a href="./FeathinSilyar">FeathinSilyar</a>:  So score another level 7 realm.  Apparently likelihoods of a weapon getting a higher realm isn't supposed to be influenced by which weapon it is, so Mormegil isn't any more likely to gain the higher realms than the daggers.<br>
Garachoth is in italics there to denote that it is not in the current ToME, but  will appear in 3.0.  As per the main artifacts page anyway.  So yeah, I think it is impossible to currently get. 
