    <a href="./BadPazzword">BadPazzword</a>: Cleared Garachoth out in the main article. 
                </ul>            </ul>


<p>
<strong><a href="./RedNaga">RedNaga</a></strong>: just on a chatter basis, but which good would ever come to a weapon from the 'unaffected by cold/electricity' flags? AFAIK no weapon is even checked for destruction by those two damage types. 
</p>
<p>
Limpy: are you sure that you get (+2,+1) when the weapon level's up? im currently using Narthanc and it just got (+1,+1), dunno if its with the counter or without though.  
</p>

    <ul>

 <strong><a href="./FeathinSilyar">FeathinSilyar</a></strong>:  Yeah, I'm actually sure that it varies more than stated there.  Just hadn't gotten around to changing it.  That's done now. 
        <ul>

  <strong>Actius</strong>: I peeked at the source, and there's only three basic possibilities (roughly even chances of each):  The first possibility is as described above (+1,+1 or +2,+1).  The second possibility is mostly right (+1,+0, gain a point towards buying a flag group) -- and it's only for in possibility that the weapon gains a realm.  But the third possibility is totally described wrong: here the weapon gains pval (up to a limit of +5) and gains a power from a realm (if it doesn't already have a realm, it gets one).  In other words, the chances of these things aren't independent. 
        </ul>    </ul>


<p>
<strong>Eric Xanthus</strong>: I've posted this in the forum spoilers and oook, but it bears mentioning here too.  I got Antimagic realm on Mormegil today (7-22-05). 
